<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-26T09:14:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-26T09:14:00-05:00" n="393" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/362.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-26T09:00:00-05:14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1914, 9 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>President Plaza left here Sunday night ostensibly to take command of army
                            at Esmeraldas. Mr. Pallares, President of the Chamber of Deputies, is
                            acting as President.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
